ImageKit provides a hosted remote MCP server that is managed and maintained by ImageKit. This eliminates the need to run and maintain your own local server, making it easier to get started with ImageKit&#x27;s API through your favorite AI assistant.
 The remote MCP server is available at: https://api-mcp.imagekit.in/sse 
 You&#x27;ll need a private API key from your ImageKit account and an MCP client like Claude Desktop , Claude Web , Cursor , or Windsurf .
 Claude Web
 Claude Desktop
 Cursor
 Windsurf
 To connect Claude Web to the ImageKit MCP server:
 Open Claude Web. Go to Settings → Connectors. Click "+ Add Custom Connector". Add the MCP server URL: https://api-mcp.imagekit.in/sse . Claude Desktop requires the mcp-remote package to connect to remote MCP servers.
 Edit your Claude Desktop configuration file:
 macOS : ~/Library/Application Support/Claude/claude_desktop_config.json Windows : %APPDATA%\Claude\claude_desktop_config.json Add the following configuration:
 Copy {
 "mcpServers": {
 "imagekit_api": {
 "command": "npx",
 "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote@latest", "https://api-mcp.imagekit.in/sse"]
 }
 }
}
 Restart Claude Desktop to see the MCP server connection (look for the hammer icon). Edit your Cursor MCP configuration file at ~/.cursor/mcp.json .
 Add the following configuration:
 Copy {
 "mcpServers": {
 "imagekit_api": {
 "command": "npx",
 "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote@latest", "https://api-mcp.imagekit.in/sse"]
 }
 }
}
 Edit your Windsurf configuration file at ~/.codeium/windsurf/mcp_config.json .
 Add the following configuration:
 Copy {
 "mcpServers": {
 "imagekit_api": {
 "command": "npx",
 "args": ["-y", "mcp-remote@latest", "https://api-mcp.imagekit.in/sse"]
 }
 }
}
