 }]
}
 Open method The open() method opens the widget programmatically, allowing you to override mlSettings and the callback function.
 Method signature: 
 Copy mediaLibraryWidget.open(settings?, callback?)
 Parameters: 
 Parameter Type Description settings (optional) object Object containing only mlSettings property. See mlSettings options for available configuration. The mlSettings object completely replaces the existing mlSettings from the constructor (does not merge). callback (optional) function Callback function that overrides the constructor callback. Receives the same payload structure as the constructor callback. Example usage: 
 Copy // Open widget
mediaLibraryWidget.open();

// Open with updated configuration and custom callback
mediaLibraryWidget.open({
 mlSettings: {
 initialView: {
 fileType: &#x27;images&#x27;
 },
 multiple: false
 }
}, (payload) => {
 console.log(&#x27;Custom callback:&#x27;, payload.data);
});

// Open with default settings
mediaLibraryWidget.open({});
 Note: When you provide mlSettings to the open() method, it completely replaces the existing mlSettings from the constructor. It does not merge with existing settings. If you want to preserve some settings while updating others, you must include all desired settings in the mlSettings object will calling open() .
