 Opening programmatically

When renderOpenButton is set to false , you can control the widget programmatically using the open() method. This is useful when you want to:
 Use custom buttons or triggers in your application Open the widget with different configurations based on context Integrate with editor plugins or CMS interfaces Example: 
 Copy // Initialize widget without default button
const mediaLibraryWidget = new IKMediaLibraryWidget({
 container: &#x27;#container&#x27;,
 view: &#x27;modal&#x27;,
 renderOpenButton: false // Hide default button
}, (payload) => {
 console.log(&#x27;Selected assets:&#x27;, payload.data);
});

// Open with custom button
document.getElementById(&#x27;myCustomButton&#x27;).addEventListener(&#x27;click&#x27;, () => {
 mediaLibraryWidget.open({
 mlSettings: {
 initialView: {
 fileType: &#x27;images&#x27;
 }
 }
 });
});
