 Generating signed URLs

If your account has restrict unsigned URLs enabled, or if you are delivering private files , every resource (video, poster, seek thumbnails, subtitles etc.) URL the player loads must be signed.
 The player handles this through a signer function that you provide:
 Copy type SignerFn = (url: string) => Promise<string>;
 The player calls your function each time it needs to load a resource, not once upfront. This means you can return short-lived signed URLs — every new resource load gets a fresh signature.
 Sign on the server, never in the browser. Signing requires your ImageKit private key , which must never be shipped to the client. Expose an endpoint in your backend that performs the signing — either using one of ImageKit&#x27;s server-side SDKs , or by implementing it yourself following the signed URL generation guide — and call it from signerFn .
 JavaScript
 React
 Vue
 Astro
 Copy import { videoPlayer } from &#x27;@imagekit/video-player&#x27;;
import &#x27;@imagekit/video-player/styles.css&#x27;;

const player = videoPlayer(&#x27;my-video&#x27;, {
 imagekitId: &#x27;YOUR_IMAGEKIT_ID&#x27;,
 signerFn: async (url) => {
 const res = await fetch(&#x27;/api/sign&#x27;, {
 method: &#x27;POST&#x27;,
 headers: { &#x27;Content-Type&#x27;: &#x27;application/json&#x27; },
 body: JSON.stringify({ url }),
 });
 return await res.text(); // signed URL as plain text
 },
});

player.src({ src: &#x27;https://ik.imagekit.io/<your-imagekit-id>/private-video.mp4&#x27; });
