 Endpoint contract — your /api/sign route must:
 Accept POST with a JSON body { url: string, ...body } . Return the signed URL as plain text in the response body with a 2xx status. signerOptions also accepts:
 Field Description url (required) Endpoint that returns the signed URL as plain text. headers Extra request headers (e.g. a static API key). body Extra JSON fields merged with { url } in the request body. credentials fetch credentials mode. Defaults to &#x27;same-origin&#x27; , so session cookies are sent automatically for same-origin endpoints. Set signerOptions={{ mode: &#x27;imperative&#x27; }} so the component defers loading the video until you assign signerFn to the ik-video-player element from a sibling <script> . The pending source is flushed through the signer as soon as it is assigned.
